<p>I upvoted, but</p>
<blockquote>
<p>rainbow flag</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I thought we had a fairly strict 'no bringing up heated socio-political issues' rule, staff, and with no explanation, I'm pretty sure the rainbow flag Foundationball is about the gay rights movement. Otherwise it would say 'rainbow' without 'flag.'</p>
<p>Seriously, I'm all for freedom of speech in every single aspect, but I'm not comfortable with everyone on this site/in this culture being represented by that when we don't know for a fact that every site member supports what it represents. I mean, it's nothing but the rainbow flag over the Foundation logo. What else could it mean? This concerns me deeply (this site has always been apolitical, and I loved it) so I hope a staffer comes by soon. Thank you.</p>
<p>E: and let me quote this before someone else does:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>All of them are based on personal understanding of GOIs, or are simply for fun, thus don't need to be taken seriously.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Let me clarify that I am asking about site rules regarding politics. If this is supposed to be a part of Sunny's author page somehow, or something similar, and there's no rule against personal politics being shown <em>in that manner</em>, then of course I'm all good with that.</p>

							</div>

								
